docs.abstract: Obama administration eliminates National Security Entry-Exit Registration System, which was created to track visitors from countries with active terrorist groups after attacks of Sept 11, 2001, and has been out of use for years; largely symbolic move distances Obama from any effort by Pres-elect Donald Trump to create similar registries.
